{"title": "In Our Convent Days", "description": "With her usual wit and charm, Ms. Repplier recalls her days at Eden Hall, the Convent of the Sacred Heart in Torresdale, north of Philadelphia. She shares the highlights (and some of the low lights) of her time there. Perhaps this sharp eye, nurtured by her willfulness and independent spirit, was the reason she was not invited to return to Eden after her second year. Not only Catholics or boarding school alumnae will find this book entertaining; anyone who went to school or who looks back on their childhood will see their own experience somewhere in this memoir. ( Summary by Mary Schneider)", "duration": 15235, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "1404", "name": "Agnes Repplier"}], "coverArt": "http://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt28/our_convent_days_1212.jpg", "copyright_year": "1905", "genres": ["Essays & Short Works", "Humor", "Memoirs"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Mary Schneider"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Mary Schneider"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Maria Therese"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Sharon Kilmer"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "1 - Introduction", "readers": [5220], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/conventdays_ms_librivox/inourconventdays_01_repplier_64kb.mp3", "duration": 168}, {"section": 2, "title": "2 - Marianus", "readers": [5220], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/conventdays_ms_librivox/inourconventdays_02_repplier_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2073}, {"section": 3, "title": "3 - On the Convent Stage", "readers": [5220], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/conventdays_ms_librivox/inourconventdays_03_repplier_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2204}, {"section": 4, "title": "4 - In Retreat", "readers": [5220], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/conventdays_ms_librivox/inourconventdays_04_repplier_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1965}, {"section": 5, "title": "5 - Un Conge sans Cloche", "readers": [5220], "path": "http://www.ar